description:
&lt;p&gt;To provide effective and efficient decontamination and distribution of re-usable medical devices for use in direct patient care which includes the dismantlement, inspection, re-assembly and function testing of invasive medical devices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we look for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Two Full Time 37.5 hours per week roles are available:- 1:00pm – 9:00pm shift Monday to Friday and 4:00pm - 12am Monday to Friday&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;9:00am - 5:00pm shift Weekend on rotation once competent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly motivated, flexible, enthusiastic and willing to learn the Decontamination process and operate SSD equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a team environment and independently as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sound written and verbal communication skills with basic computer knowledge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in a highly motivated and friendly environment Sterile Services team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training and required skills will be provided&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Career progression within field of Sterile Services and NHS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sterile Services Department supplying sterile instruments within Hospital Theatres and Departments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the trust: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The vision at Hampshire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust is to provide outstanding care for every patient. We serve a population of nearly 600,000 people across Hampshire and West Berkshire as well as some people who access our specialist services from across the country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Created in January 2012 the Foundation Trust prioritises the provision of exceptional, compassionate, care delivered by the valued staff working in a culture of collaboration and mutual respect. HHFT employs circa 6,000 people and had a turnover of £382m in 17/18&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Four core values (CARE) Compassion, Accountability, Respect and Encourage. These are in place to support of four clear objectives, provide outstanding care of patients, empowering all members of staff, sustainable growth and innovating for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
